N:genkit
D:Build and operate Genkit as the full-stack AI workflow layer for web and backend apps. Use when the user needs server-owned AI flows, tool calling, prompt files, structured outputs, RAG, evaluation, observability, or deployment to Firebase / Cloud Run / another backend runtime. Route direct Firebase app SDK integration and simple in-app Gemini features to `firebase-ai-logic`.
G:genkit firebase ai-workflows flows tool-calling rag evaluation observability cloud-run fullstack backend developer-ui dotprompt

U[6]:
  **Backend AI workflows**: own reusable server-side flows instead of client-only model calls
  **Tool calling / agents**: add deterministic actions behind a backend workflow boundary
  **Retrieval / prompts**: manage grounded workflows, prompt files, and structured outputs
  **Evaluation / observability**: use traces, Developer UI, and eval loops before rollout
  **Deployment choice**: choose Firebase vs Cloud Run vs another backend runtime deliberately
  **Routing boundary**: send direct Firebase app SDK integration to `firebase-ai-logic`

S[6]{n,action,details}:
  1,Classify layer,Decide whether the job is client integration or backend workflow ownership
  2,Choose mode,Pick flow-foundation / tool-and-agent / retrieval-and-prompt / evaluation-and-observability / deployment-runtime
  3,Freeze contract,Define one flow boundary with input/output schema and server-side responsibilities
  4,Build minimum workflow,Start with one flow and add tools/retrieval only if justified
  5,Debug with traces,Use Developer UI and representative inputs before scaling usage
  6,Deploy deliberately,Choose Firebase or Cloud Run based on ownership, clients, and security boundary

R[6]:
  Choose Genkit because you need a workflow layer, not just because the app uses Firebase
  Keep direct in-app Gemini features routed to `firebase-ai-logic`
  Start with one crisp backend flow before adding tools, RAG, or multi-agent behavior
  Use Developer UI and traces early; they are part of the framework value
  Add evals once the workflow becomes a maintained product capability
  Treat runtime choice as an architecture decision, not a copy-pasted default

E[3]{desc,in,out}:
  "Reusable backend assistant","Support app needs retrieval + one ticket tool + one endpoint reused by the web app","Use genkit with a backend flow boundary and explicit tool/retrieval plan"
  "Direct Firebase app feature","Add Gemini summaries directly inside a Firebase web app","Route to firebase-ai-logic instead of forcing Genkit"
  "Launch-readiness loop","Existing Genkit flows need evals and observability before Cloud Run rollout","Use genkit with an evidence-first eval and trace plan"
